A minibus taxi driver is in a critical condition after being involved in a collision with a bakkie on Hendrik Potgieter and Cascades roads in Strubens Valley, Roodepoort, in Johannesburg on Sunday, paramedics said. The cause of the collision was unknown and the jaws-of-life had to be used to free the driver from the taxi, ER24 spokeswoman Annine Siddall said. The man sustained multiple fractures and abdominal injuries and was airlifted by the ER24 OnePlan Medical Helicopter to a nearby hospital for further medical care. No other injuries were reported,&#8221; she said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.